As the numbers of humanity dwindle from alien bombardment, the creatures of magic, buoyed by the increase in free-floating Mana, begin to re-emerge.  he first to awaken are the elves, who have spent the last few centuries in a magical sleep.
 Their charms and arrows prove to be surprisingly effective against alien armor, and beam weapons. The next to stir are the dwarves, who have long been in hiding, and have been preparing for this day. Dwarven seige

As the numbers of humanity dwindle from alien bombardment, the creatures of magic, buoyed by the increase in free-floating Mana, begin to re-emerge.  he first to awaken are the elves, who have spent the last few centuries in a magical sleep.
 Their charms and arrows prove to be surprisingly effective against alien armor, and beam weapons. The next to stir are the dwarves, who have long been in hiding, and have been preparing for this day. Dwarven siege engines and primitive

When hostile aliens reduce humanity to a mere fraction, the survivors discover an old power has begun to reawaken once again. As the numbers of humanity dwindle from alien bombardment, the creatures of magic, buoyed by the increase in free-floating Mana, begin to re-emerge.  he first to awaken are the elves, who have spent the last few centuries in a magical sleep.
 Their charms and arrows prove to be surprisingly effective against alien armor, and beam weapons. The next to stir are the dwarves, who have long been in hiding, and have been preparing for this day. Dwarven siege engines and other primitive devices of destruction are even more effective against the aliens, and a dwarf trebuchet manages to, for the first time, bring down an alien ship.

Humans once wielded formidable magical power. But with over 7 billion of us on the planet now, Mana has spread far too thinly to have any effect. When hostile aliens reduce humanity to a mere fraction, the survivors discover an old power has begun to reawaken once again. As the numbers of humanity dwindle from alien bombardment, the creatures of magic, buoyed by the increase in free-floating Mana, begin to re-emerge.  he first to awaken are the elves, who have spent the last few centuries in a magical sleep.

As the numbers of humanity dwindle from alien bombardment, the creatures of magic, buoyed by the increase in free-floating Mana, begin to re-emerge.  he first to awaken are the elves, who have spent the last few centuries in a magical sleep.
 Their charms and arrows prove to be surprisingly effective against alien armor, and beam weapons. The next to stir are the dwarves, who have long been in hiding, and have been preparing for this day. Dwarven siege engines and other primitive devices of destruction are even more effective against the aliens, and a dwarf trebuchet manages to, for the first time, bring down an alien ship.

After that, the goblins and other darker magical creatures begin to stir. Though long enemies of both man, and the other magical beings, they join forces with the other survivors to fight the alien menace, and th

When hostile aliens reduce humanity to a mere fraction, the survivors discover an old power has begun to reawaken once again. As the numbers of humanity dwindle from alien bombardment, the creatures of magic, buoyed by the increase in free-floating Mana, begin to re-emerge.  he first to awaken are the elves, who have spent the last few centuries in a magical sleep.
 Their charms and arrows prove to be surprisingly effective against alien armor, and beam weapons. The next to stir are the dwarves, who have long been in hiding, and have been preparing for this day. Dwarven siege engines and other primitive devices of destruction are even more effective against the aliens, and a dwarf trebuchet manages to, for the first time, bring down an alien ship.

The next to stir are the dwarves, who have long been in hiding, and have been preparing for this day. Dwarven siege engines and other primitive devices of destruction are even more effective against the aliens, and a dwarf trebuchet manages to, for the first time, bring down an alien ship.

After that, the goblins and other darker magical creatures begin to stir. Though long enemies of both man, and the other magical beings, they join forces with the other survivors to fight the alien menace, and their poison darts wreak havoc among the ranks of the alien troops. Finally, the dragons, the oldest of all magical creatures, awaken from their slumber. Humans once wielded formidable magical power. But with over 7 billion of us on the planet now, Mana has spread far too thinly to have any effect. When hostile aliens reduce humanity to a mere fraction, the survivors discover an old power has begun to reawaken once again. As the numbers of humanity dwindle from alien bombardment, the creatures of magic, buoyed by the increase in free-floating Mana, begin to re-emerge.  he first to awaken are the elves, who have spent the last few centuries in a magical sleep.
 Their charms and arrows prove to be surprisingly effective against alien armor, and beam weapons. The next to stir are the dwarves, who have long been in hiding, and have been preparing for this day. Dwarven siege engines and other primitive devices of destruction are even more effective against the aliens, and a dwarf trebuchet manages to, for the first time, bring down an alien ship.

Humans once wielded formidable magical power. But with over 7 billion of us on the planet now, Mana has spread far too thinly to have any effect. When hostile aliens reduce humanity to a mere fraction, the survivors discover an old power has begun to reawaken once again. As the numbers of humanity dwindle from alien bombardment, the creatures of magic, buoyed by the increase in free-floating Mana, begin to re-emerge.  he first to awaken are the elves, who have spent the last few centuries in a magical sleep.
 Their charms and arrows prove to be surprisingly effective against alien armor, and beam weapons. The next to stir are the dwarves, who have long been in hiding, and have been preparing for this day. Dwarven siege engines and other primitive devices of destruction are even more effective against the aliens, and a dwarf trebuchet manages to, for the first time, bring down an alien ship.

When hostile aliens reduce humanity to a mere fraction, the survivors discover an old power has begun to reawaken once again. As the numbers of humanity dwindle from alien bombardment, the creatures of magic, buoyed by the increase in free-floating Mana, begin to re-emerge.  he first to awaken are the elves, who have spent the last few centuries in a magical sleep.
 Their charms and arrows prove to be surprisingly effective against alien armor, and beam weapons. The next to stir are the dwarves, who have long been in hiding, and have been preparing for this day. Dwarven siege engines and other primitive devices of destruction are even more effective against the aliens, and a dwarf trebuchet manages to, for the first time, bring down an alien ship.

After that, the goblins and other darker magical creatures begin to stir. Though long enemies of both man, and the other magical beings, they join forces with the other survivors to fight the alien menace, and their poison darts wreak havoc among the ranks of the alien troops. Finally, the dragons, the oldest of all magical creatures, awaken from their slumber. Their fiery breath and claws are devastating against the aliens, and their armored scales are proof against their weapons. The next to stir are the dwarves, who have long been in hiding, and have been preparing for this day. Dwarven siege engines and other primitive devices of destruction are even more effective against the aliens, and a dwarf trebuchet manages to, for the first time, bring down an alien ship.

After that, the goblins and other darker magical creatures begin to stir. Though long enemies of both man, and the other magical beings, they join forces with the other survivors to fight the alien menace, and their poison darts wreak havoc among the ranks of the alien troops. Finally, the dragons, the oldest of all magical creatures, awaken from their slumber. Their fiery breath and claws are devastating against the aliens, and their armored scales are proof against their weapons. The mere presence of the creatures often makes the most battle-hardened alien warriors flee in terror. Meanwhile, the humans begin to discover their own latent magical abilities. Now human mages can join in the battle,

As the numbers of humanity dwindle from alien bombardment, the creatures of magic, buoyed by the increase in free-floating Mana, begin to re-emerge.  he first to awaken are the elves, who have spent the last few centuries in a magical sleep.
 Their charms and arrows prove to be surprisingly effective against alien armor, and beam weapons. The next to stir are the dwarves, who have long been in hiding, and have been preparing for this day. Dwarven siege engines and other primitive devices of destruction are even more effective against the aliens, and a dwarf trebuchet manages to, for the first time, bring down an alien ship.

After that, the goblins and other darker magical creatures begin to stir. Though long enemies of both man, and the other magical beings, they join forces with the other survivors to fight the alien menace, and their poison darts wreak havoc among the ranks of the alien troops. Finally, the dragons, the oldest of all magical creatures, awaken from their slumber. Their fiery breath and claws are devastating against the aliens, and their armored scales are proof against their weapons. The mere presence of the creatures often makes the most battle-hardened alien warriors flee in terror. Meanwhile, the humans begin to discover their own latent magical abilities. Now human mages can join in the battle, and their spells are the fi

Humans once wielded formidable magical power. But with over 7 billion of us on the planet now, Mana has spread far too thinly to have any effect. When hostile aliens reduce humanity to a mere fraction, the survivors discover an old power has begun to reawaken once again. As the numbers of humanity dwindle from alien bombardment, the creatures of magic, buoyed by the increase in free-floating Mana, begin to re-emerge.  he first to awaken are the elves, who have spent the last few centuries in a magical sleep.
 Their charms and arrows prove to be surprisingly effective against alien armor, and beam weapons. The next to stir are the dwarves, who have long been in hiding, and have been preparing for this day. Dwarven siege engines and other primitive devices of destruction are even more effective against the aliens, and a dwarf trebuchet manages to, for the first time, bring down an alien ship.

After that, the goblins and other darker magical creatures begin to stir. Though long enemies of both man, and the other magical beings, they join forces with the other survivors to fight the alien menace, and their poison darts wreak havoc among the ranks of the alien troops.  Their charms and arrows prove to be surprisingly effective against alien armor, and beam weapons. The next to stir are the dwarves, who have long been in hiding, and have been preparing for this day. Dwarven siege engines and other primitive devices of destruction are even more effective against the aliens, and a dwarf trebuchet manages to, for the first time, bring down an alien ship.

After that, the goblins and other darker magical creatures begin to stir. Though long enemies of both man, and the other magical beings, they join forces with the other survivors to fight the alien menace, and their poison darts wreak havoc among the ranks of the alien troops. Finally, the dragons, the oldest of all magical creatures, awaken from their slumber. Their fiery breath and claws are devastating against the aliens, and their armored scales are proof against their weapons. The mere presence of the creatures often makes the most battle-hardened alien warriors flee in terror. Meanwhile, the humans begin to discover their own latent magical abilities. Now human mages can join in the battle, and their spells are the final ingredient that helps turn the tide of the war.

When hostile aliens reduce humanity to a mere fraction, the survivors discover an old power has begun to reawaken once again. As the numbers of humanity dwindle from alien bombardment, the creatures of magic, buoyed by the increase in free-floating Mana, begin to re-emerge.  he first to awaken are the elves, who have spent the last few centuries in a magical sleep.
 Their charms and arrows prove to be surprisingly effective against alien armor, and beam weapons. The next to stir are the dwarves, who have long been in hiding, and have been preparing for this day. Dwarven siege engines and other primitive devices of destruction are even more effective against the aliens, and a dwarf trebuchet manages to, for the first time, bring down an alien ship.

After that, the goblins and other darker magical creatures begin to stir. Though long enemies of both man, and the other magical beings, they join forces with the other survivors to fight the alien menace, and their poison darts wreak havoc among the ranks of the alien troops. Finally, the dragons, the oldest of all magical creatures, awaken from their slumber. Their fiery breath and claws are devastating against the aliens, and their armored scales are proof against their weapons. The mere presence of the creatures often makes the most battle-hardened alien warriors flee in terror. Meanwhile, the humans begin to discover their own latent magical abilities. Now human mages can join in the battle, and their spells are the final ingredient that helps turn the tide of the war.

When hostile aliens reduce humanity to a mere fraction, the survivors discover an old power has begun to reawaken once again. As the numbers of humanity dwindle from alien bombardment, the creatures of magic, buoyed by the increase in free-floating Mana, begin to re-emerge.  he first to awaken are the elves, who have spent the last few centuries in a magical sleep.
 Their charms and arrows prove to be surprisingly effective against alien armor, and beam weapons. The next to stir are the dwarves, who have long been in hiding, and have been preparing for this day. Dwarven siege engines and other primitive devices of destruction are even more effective against the aliens, and a dwarf trebuchet manages to, for the first time, bring down an alien ship.

After that, the goblins and other darker magical creatures begin to stir. Though long enemies of both man, and the other magical beings, they join forces with the other survivors to fight the alien menace, and their poison darts wreak havoc among the ranks of the alien troops. Finally, the dragons, the oldest of all magical creatures, awaken from their slumber. Their fiery breath and claws are devastating against the aliens, and their armored scales are proof against their weapons. The mere presence of the creatures often makes the most battle-hardened alien warriors flee in terror. Meanwhile, the humans begin to discover their own latent magical abilities. Now human mages can join in the battle, and their spells are the final ingredient that helps turn the tide of the war.

Humans once wielded formidable magical power. But with over 7 billion of us on the planet now, Mana has spread far too thinly to have any effect. When hostile aliens reduce humanity to a mere fraction, the survivors discover an old power has begun to reawaken once again. As the numbers of humanity dwindle from alien bombardment, the creatures of magic, buoyed by the increase in free-floating Mana, begin to re-emerge.  he first to awaken are the elves, who have spent the last few centuries in a magical sleep.
 Their charms and arrows prove to be surprisingly effective against alien armor, and beam weapons. The next to stir are the dwarves, who have long been in hiding, and have been preparing for this day. Dwarven siege engines and other primitive devices of destruction are even more effective against the aliens, and a dwarf trebuchet manages to, for the first time, bring down an alien ship.

After that, the goblins and other darker magical creatures begin to stir. Though long enemies of both man, and the other magical beings, they join forces with the other survivors to fight the alien menace, and their poison darts wreak havoc among the ranks of the alien troops. Humans once wielded formidable magical power. But with over 7 billion of us on the planet now, Mana has spread far too thinly to have any effect. When hostile aliens reduce humanity to a mere fraction, the survivors discover an old power has begun to reawaken once again. As the numbers of humanity dwindle from alien bombardment, the creatures of magic, buoyed by the increase in free-floating Mana, begin to re-emerge.  he first to awaken are the elves, who have spent the last few centuries in a magical sleep.
 Their charms and arrows prove to be surprisingly effective against alien armor, and beam weapons. The next to stir are the dwarves, who have long been in hiding, and have been preparing for this day. Dwarven siege engines and other primitive devices of destruction are even more effective against the aliens, and a dwarf trebuchet manages to, for the first time, bring down an alien ship.

After that, the goblins and other darker magical creatures begin to stir. Though long enemies of both man, and the other magical beings, they join forces with the other survivors to fight the alien menace, and their poison darts wreak havoc among the ranks of the alien troops. Finally, the dragons, the oldest of all magical creatures, awaken from their slumber. Their fiery breath and claws are devastating against the aliens, and their armored scales are proof against their weapons. The mere presence of the creatures often makes the most battle-hardened alien warriors flee in terror. Meanwhile, the humans begin to discover their own latent magical abilities. Now human mages can join in the battle, and their spells are the final ingredient that helps turn the tide of the war.

When hostile aliens reduce humanity to a mere fraction, the survivors discover an old power has begun to reawaken once again. As the numbers of humanity dwindle from alien bombardment, the creatures of magic, buoyed by the increase in free-floating Mana, begin to re-emerge.  he first to awaken are the elves, who have spent the last few centuries in a magical sleep.
 Their charms and arrows prove to be surprisingly effective against alien armor, and beam weapons. The next to stir are the dwarves, who have long been in hiding, and have been preparing for this day. Dwarven siege engines and other primitive devices of destruction are even more effective against the aliens, and a dwarf trebuchet manages to, for the first time, bring down an alien ship.

After that, the goblins and other darker magical creatures begin to stir. Though long enemies of both man, and the other magical beings, they join forces with the other survivors to fight the alien menace, and their poison darts wreak havoc among the ranks of the alien troops. Finally, the dragons, the oldest of all magical creatures, awaken from their slumber. Their fiery breath and claws are devastating against the aliens, and their armored scales are proof against their weapons. The mere presence of the creatures often makes the most battle-hardened alien warriors flee in terror. Meanwhile, the humans begin to discover their own latent magical abilities. Now human mages can join in the battle, and their spells are the final ingredient that helps turn the tide of the war.

Within a few years, the aliens are defeated, and the survivors are able to begin rebuilding their civilization. But now, humanity is no longer sole master of the planet. The magical creatures have returned, and they are not willing to give up their new-found freedom. They remember their ancient defeat at the hands of man, and resent it, and before long a new war breaks out. The magical creatures are far more powerful than humanity, and the war d

Humans once wielded formidable magical power. But with over 7 billion of us on the planet now, Mana has spread far too thinly to have any effect. When hostile aliens reduce humanity to a mere fraction, the survivors discover an old power has begun to reawaken once again. As the numbers of humanity dwindle from alien bombardment, the creatures of magic, buoyed by the increase in free-floating Mana, begin to re-emerge.  he first to awaken are the elves, who have spent the last few centuries in a magical sleep.
 Their charms and arrows prove to be surprisingly effective against alien armor, and beam weapons. The next to stir are the dwarves, who have long been in hiding, and have been preparing for this day. Dwarven siege engines and other primitive devices of destruction are even more effective against the aliens, and a dwarf trebuchet manages to, for the first time, bring down an alien ship.

After that, the goblins and other darker magical creatures begin to stir. Though long enemies of both man, and the other magical beings, they join forces with the other survivors to fight the alien menace, and their poison darts wreak havoc among the ranks of the alien troops. Finally, the dragons, the oldest of all magical creatures, awaken from their slumber. Their fiery breath and claws are devastating against the aliens, and their armored scales are proof against their weapons. The mere presence of the creatures often makes the most battle-hardened alien warriors flee in terror. Meanwhile, the humans begin to discover their own latent magical abilities. Now human mages can join in the battle, and their spells are the final ingredient that helps turn the tide of the war.

Within a few years, the aliens are defeated, and the survivors are able to begin rebuilding their civilization. But now, humanity is no longer sole master of the planet. The magical creatures have returned, and they are not willing to give up their new-found freedom. As the numbers of humanity dwindle from alien bombardment, the creatures of magic, buoyed by the increase in free-floating Mana, begin to re-emerge.  he first to awaken are the elves, who have spent the last few centuries in a magical sleep.
 Their charms and arrows prove to be surprisingly effective against alien armor, and beam weapons. The next to stir are the dwarves, who have long been in hiding, and have been preparing for this day. Dwarven siege engines and other primitive devices of destruction are even more effective against the aliens, and a dwarf trebuchet manages to, for the first time, bring down an alien ship.

After that, the goblins and other darker magical creatures begin to stir. Though long enemies of both man, and the other magical beings, they join forces with the other survivors to fight the alien menace, and their poison darts wreak havoc among the ranks of the alien troops. Finally, the dragons, the oldest of all magical creatures, awaken from their slumber. Their fiery breath and claws are devastating against the aliens, and their armored scales are proof against their weapons. The mere presence of the creatures often makes the most battle-hardened alien warriors flee in terror. Meanwhile, the humans begin to discover their own latent magical abilities. Now human mages can join in the battle, and their spells are the final ingredient that helps turn the tide of the war.

Within a few years, the aliens are defeated, and the survivors are able to begin rebuilding their civilization. But now, humanity is no longer sole master of the planet. The magical creatures have returned, and they are not willing to give up their new-found freedom. They remember their ancient defeat at the hands of man, and resent it, and before long a new war breaks out. The magical creatures are far more powerful than humanity, and the war does not go well for the humans.  Before long, the humans lose, and decisively, and are forced to

As the numbers of humanity dwindle from alien bombardment, the creatures of magic, buoyed by the increase in free-floating Mana, begin to re-emerge.  he first to awaken are the elves, who have spent the last few centuries in a magical sleep.
 Their charms and arrows prove to be surprisingly effective against alien armor, and beam weapons. The next to stir are the dwarves, who have long been in hiding, and have been preparing for this day. Dwarven siege engines and other primitive devices of destruction are even more effective against the aliens, and a dwarf trebuchet manages to, for the first time, bring down an alien ship.

After that, the goblins and other darker magical creatures begin to stir. Though long enemies of both man, and the other magical beings, they join forces with the other survivors to fight the alien menace, and their poison darts wreak havoc among the ranks of the alien troops. Finally, the dragons, the oldest of all magical creatures, awaken from their slumber. Their fiery breath and claws are devastating against the aliens, and their armored scales are proof against their weapons. The mere presence of the creatures often makes the most battle-hardened alien warriors flee in terror. Meanwhile, the humans begin to discover their own latent magical abilities. Now human mages can join in the battle, and their spells are the final ingredient that helps turn the tide of the war.

Within a few years, the aliens are defeated, and the survivors are able to begin rebuilding their civilization. But now, humanity is no longer sole master of the planet. The magical creatures have returned, and they are not willing to give up their new-found freedom. They remember their ancient defeat at the hands of man, and resent it, and before long a new war breaks out. The magical creatures are far more powerful than humanity, and the war does not go well for the humans.  Before long, the humans lose, and decisively, and are forced to surrender uncondi

Humans once wielded formidable magical power. But with over 7 billion of us on the planet now, Mana has spread far too thinly to have any effect. When hostile aliens reduce humanity to a mere fraction, the survivors discover an old power has begun to reawaken once again. As the numbers of humanity dwindle from alien bombardment, the creatures of magic, buoyed by the increase in free-floating Mana, begin to re-emerge.  he first to awaken are the elves, who have spent the last few centuries in a magical sleep.
 Their charms and arrows prove to be surprisingly effective against alien armor, and beam weapons. The next to stir are the dwarves, who have long been in hiding, and have been preparing for this day. Dwarven siege engines and other primitive devices of destruction are even more effective against the aliens, and a dwarf trebuchet manages to, for the first time, bring down an alien ship.

After that, the goblins and other darker magical creatures begin to stir. Though long enemies of both man, and the other magical beings, they join forces with the other survivors to fight the alien menace, and their poison darts wreak havoc among the ranks of the alien troops. Finally, the dragons, the oldest of all magical creatures, awaken from their slumber. Their fiery breath and claws are devastating against the aliens, and their armored scales are proof against their weapons. The mere presence of the creatures often makes the most battle-hardened alien warriors flee in terror. Meanwhile, the humans begin to discover their own latent magical abilities. Now human mages can join in the battle, and their spells are the final ingredient that helps turn the tide of the war.

Within a few years, the aliens are defeated, and the survivors are able to begin rebuilding their civilization. But now, humanity is no longer sole master of the planet. The magical creatures have returned, and they are not willing to give up their new-found freedom. They remember their ancient defeat at the hands of man, and resent it, and before long a new war breaks out. The magical creatures are far more powerful than humanity, and the war does not go well for the humans.  Before long, the humans lose, and decisively, and are forced to surrender unconditionally.

Humans once wielded formidable magical power. But with over 7 billion of us on the planet now, Mana has spread far too thinly to have any effect. When hostile aliens reduce humanity to a mere fraction, the survivors discover an old power has begun to reawaken once again. As the numbers of humanity dwindle from alien bombardment, the creatures of magic, buoyed by the increase in free-floating Mana, begin to re-emerge.  he first to awaken are the elves, who have spent the last few centuries in a magical sleep.
 Their charms and arrows prove to be surprisingly effective against alien armor, and beam weapons. The next to stir are the dwarves, who have long been in hiding, and have been preparing for this day. Dwarven siege engines and other primitive devices of destruction are even more effective against the aliens, and a dwarf trebuchet manages to, for the first time, bring down an alien ship.

After that, the goblins and other darker magical creatures begin to stir. Though long enemies of both man, and the other magical beings, they join forces with the other survivors to fight the alien menace, and their poison darts wreak havoc among the ranks of the alien troops. Finally, the dragons, the oldest of all magical creatures, awaken from their slumber. Their fiery breath and claws are devastating against the aliens, and their armored scales are proof against their weapons. The mere presence of the creatures often makes the most battle-hardened alien warriors flee in terror. Meanwhile, the humans begin to discover their own latent magical abilities. Now human mages can join in the battle, and their spells are the final ingredient that helps turn the tide of the war.

 Their charms and arrows prove to be surprisingly effective against alien armor, and beam weapons. The next to stir are the dwarves, who have long been in hiding, and have been preparing for this day. Dwarven siege engines and other primitive devices of destruction are even more effective against the aliens, and a dwarf trebuchet manages to, for the first time, bring down an alien ship.

After that, the goblins and other darker magical creatures begin to stir. Though long enemies of both man, and the other magical beings, they join forces with the other survivors to fight the alien menace, and their poison darts wreak havoc among the ranks of the alien troops. Finally, the dragons, the oldest of all magical creatures, awaken from their slumber. Their fiery breath and claws are devastating against the aliens, and their armored scales are proof against their weapons. The mere presence of the creatures often makes the most battle-hardened alien warriors flee in terror. Meanwhile, the humans begin to discover their own latent magical abilities. Now human mages can join in the battle, and their spells are the final ingredient that helps turn the tide of the war.

Within a few years, the aliens are defeated, and the survivors are able to begin rebuilding their civilization. But now, humanity is no longer sole master of the planet. The magical creatures have returned, and they are not willing to give up their new-found freedom. They remember their ancient defeat at the hands of man, and resent it, and before long a new war breaks out. The magical creatures are far more powerful than humanity, and the war does not go well for the humans.  Before long, the humans lose, and decisively, and are forced to surrender unconditionally.

The war finally ends, with the last survivors of humanity forced to cling to a mise

Humans once wielded formidable magical power. But with over 7 billion of us on the planet now, Mana has spread far too thinly to have any effect. When hostile aliens reduce humanity to a mere fraction, the survivors discover an old power has begun to reawaken once again. As the numbers of humanity dwindle from alien bombardment, the creatures of magic, buoyed by the increase in free-floating Mana, begin to re-emerge.  he first to awaken are the elves, who have spent the last few centuries in a magical sleep.
 Their charms and arrows prove to be surprisingly effective against alien armor, and beam weapons. The next to stir are the dwarves, who have long been in hiding, and have been preparing for this day. Dwarven siege engines and other primitive devices of destruction are even more effective against the aliens, and a dwarf trebuchet manages to, for the first time, bring down an alien ship.

After that, the goblins and other darker magical creatures begin to stir. Though long enemies of both man, and the other magical beings, they join forces with the other survivors to fight the alien menace, and their poison darts wreak havoc among the ranks of the alien troops.
